<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Here are the <strong>5 problems</strong> you should document (write these in your own words):</p>
<div class="overflow-x-auto w-full px-2 mb-6"><table class="min-w-full border-collapse text-sm leading-[1.7] whitespace-normal"><thead class="text-left"><tr><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">#</th><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Problem</th><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Why it's a problem</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">1</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">calculateTotal()</code> has hardcoded discount if-else chain</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Adding a new discount requires modifying this class — violates OCP</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">2</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">ShoppingCart</code> handles both cart state AND discount logic</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Single Responsibility Principle violation — two reasons to change</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">3</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Discount types are stringly-typed (<code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">"WELCOME10"</code>, <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">"BLACKFRIDAY"</code>)</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">No type safety; typos silently do nothing</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">4</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">No abstraction for discounts</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Can't add a discount without touching ShoppingCart's internals</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">5</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Discount logic is not testable in isolation</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">You can't unit test <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">WELCOME10</code> without a full cart</td></tr></tbody></table></div>
<h4 class="text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold">Step 5: Ask the AI (me!) and compare</h4>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Here's the prompt the assignment suggests you use — paste your messy code and ask:</p>
<blockquote class="ml-2 border-l-4 border-border-300/10 pl-4 text-text-300">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">"Bu kodda hangi tasarım sorunlarını görüyorsun? Hangi tasarım örüntüleri bu sorunları çözebilir?"</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Then in PROBLEMS.md, add a section comparing what you found vs. what I said.</p>
