iv class="font-claude-response relative leading-[1.65rem] [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:bg-bg-000/50 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-0.5 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-border-400 [&amp;_.ignore-pre-bg&gt;div]:bg-transparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Yes! Before the cmd step, you need to create the repo on GitHub first.</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to <strong>github.com</strong> and sign in</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click the <strong>+</strong> button (top right) → <strong>New repository</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Name it <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">eticaret-sepeti</code></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Set it to <strong>Public</strong> (required by the assignment)</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Do NOT</strong> check "Add a README" — leave everything unchecked</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Create repository</strong></li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">GitHub will then show you a page with commands. Don't do anything there yet — just copy the URL at the top, it'll look like:</p>
<div role="group" aria-label="Code" tabindex="0" class="relative group/copy bg-bg-000/50 border-0.5 border-border-400 rounded-lg focus:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-accent-100"><div class="sticky opacity-0 group-hover/copy:opacity-100 group-focus-within/copy:opacity-100 top-2 py-2 h-12 w-0 float-right"><div class="absolute right-0 h-8 px-2 items-center inline-flex z-10"><button class="inline-flex
