e on GitHub now!</h2><div class="font-claude-response relative leading-[1.65rem] [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:bg-bg-000/50 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-0.5 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-border-400 [&amp;_.ignore-pre-bg&gt;div]:bg-transparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Nice, you're on GitHub now!</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Next step is creating <strong>PROBLEMS.md</strong> — this is the core deliverable of Phase 0.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">In Eclipse, right-click your project → <strong>New → File</strong> → name it <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">PROBLEMS.md</code> → Finish.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Then paste this in and <strong>fill in the blanks in your own words</strong> (the assignment checks that it's yours):</p>
