span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> AI Log — Phase 1: Creational Patterns</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> Prompt I Asked</span><span>
</span></span><span>"Bu kodda hangi tasarım sorunlarını görüyorsun? Hangi tasarım örüntüleri 
</span><span>bu sorunları çözebilir? Her sorun için kısa bir açıklama yaz."
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> AI's Answer (Summary)</span><span>
</span></span><span>AI identified 5 structural problems matching my own analysis:
</span><span>OCP violation, SRP violation, stringly-typed discounts, no discount 
</span><span>abstraction, and discounts cannot be combined. It also caught a bonus 
</span><span>issue I missed: the BUY_2_GET_1 rule applies a flat $10 discount instead 
</span><span>of actually giving the cheapest item free.
</span><span>
</span><span>For Phase 1, AI recommended applying Factory Method to move discount 
</span><span>object creation out of ShoppingCart into a dedicated DiscountFactory class.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> What I Implemented and Why</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">###</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> Pattern: Factory Method</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Where:</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span> </span><span class="token token code-snippet code" style="color: rgb(204, 123, 244);">`DiscountFactory.java`</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Why I chose it:</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span> ShoppingCart was directly instantiating discount 
</span></span><span>behavior inline via if-else. Factory Method centralizes object creation 
</span><span>so ShoppingCart no longer needs to know which discount class to use.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">How it works:</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">-</span><span> </span><span class="token token code-snippet code" style="color: rgb(204, 123, 244);">`DiscountStrategy`</span><span> interface defines </span><span class="token token code-snippet code" style="color: rgb(204, 123, 244);">`apply(double total)`</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">-</span><span> Each discount is its own class (WelcomeDiscount, BlackFridayDiscount, etc.)
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">-</span><span> </span><span class="token token code-snippet code" style="color: rgb(204, 123, 244);">`DiscountFactory.getDiscount(String type)`</span><span> returns the correct object
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">-</span><span> ShoppingCart calls the factory instead of checking strings itself
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> Did I Copy the AI Output?</span><span>
</span></span><span>No. AI suggested the pattern and explained the concept. I wrote each 
</span><span>class myself after understanding the structure.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> Difference from AI Suggestion</span><span>
</span></span><span>[ write here if you implemented anything differently from what I suggested,
</span><span>or write "I followed the suggested structure" if you did ]</span></code></pre></div></div>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Once you paste this in, we'll start writing the actual Java code for Phase 1. Ready?</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
