span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> PATTERNS.md</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> Phase 1 — Factory Method</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">###</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> Where</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token code-snippet code" style="color: rgb(204, 123, 244);">`DiscountFactory.java`</span><span> — creates and returns the correct 
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token code-snippet code" style="color: rgb(204, 123, 244);">`DiscountStrategy`</span><span> object based on a string input.
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">###</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> Why</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token code-snippet code" style="color: rgb(204, 123, 244);">`ShoppingCart`</span><span> was directly handling discount logic with if-else blocks.
</span></span><span><span>Every new discount required modifying </span><span class="token token code-snippet code" style="color: rgb(204, 123, 244);">`ShoppingCart`</span><span>, violating OCP.
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">###</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> What We Gained</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">-</span><span> </span><span class="token token code-snippet code" style="color: rgb(204, 123, 244);">`ShoppingCart`</span><span> no longer knows about any discount class
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">-</span><span> Adding a new discount = creating one new class + one line in the factory
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">-</span><span> Each discount is testable in isolation</span></span></code></pre></div></div>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Done with both?</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
