span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> AI Log — Phase 2: Structural Patterns</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> Prompt I Asked</span><span>
</span></span><span>"Adapter pattern burada uygun mu, yoksa Facade mı? Decorator ile 
</span><span>Facade arasındaki farkı açıkla."
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> AI's Answer (Summary)</span><span>
</span></span><span>AI recommended Facade over Adapter because there is no incompatible 
</span><span>interface to adapt — the codebase is already consistent. Facade was 
</span><span>more appropriate to hide the complexity of cart, factory, and discount 
</span><span>logic behind one simple CheckoutFacade class.
</span><span>
</span><span>For combining discounts, AI recommended Decorator over Bridge because 
</span><span>Decorator wraps behavior at runtime without changing existing classes, 
</span><span>which directly solves the "discounts can't be combined" problem from 
</span><span>PROBLEMS.md.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> What I Implemented and Why</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">###</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> Pattern 1: Decorator</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Where:</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span> </span><span class="token token code-snippet code" style="color: rgb(204, 123, 244);">`DiscountDecorator.java`</span><span>, </span><span class="token token code-snippet code" style="color: rgb(204, 123, 244);">`WelcomeDecorator.java`</span><span>, </span><span class="token token code-snippet code" style="color: rgb(204, 123, 244);">`BlackFridayDecorator.java`</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Why:</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span> To solve the problem identified in Phase 0 — discounts could 
</span></span><span>not be combined. Decorator allows wrapping discounts around each other 
</span><span>at runtime without modifying any existing class.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">###</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> Pattern 2: Facade</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Where:</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span> </span><span class="token token code-snippet code" style="color: rgb(204, 123, 244);">`CheckoutFacade.java`</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Why:</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span> To hide the complexity of cart management, item creation, and 
</span></span><span>discount application behind one simple interface.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> Where AI Was Wrong or Incomplete</span><span>
</span></span><span>[write honestly here — for example: did I suggest anything that didn't 
</span><span>fit perfectly? Did you have to adjust anything? Or write what you found 
</span><span>surprising about the implementation]</span></code></pre></div></div>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Fill in the last section yourself, save, then commit everything together.</p>
