<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Phase 3 — Behavioral Patterns</strong> requires at least 2 patterns. For your cart the best fits are:</p>
<div class="overflow-x-auto w-full px-2 mb-6"><table class="min-w-full border-collapse text-sm leading-[1.7] whitespace-normal"><thead class="text-left"><tr><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Pattern</th><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Where it applies</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Strategy</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Fully replace the remaining string-based discount selection with proper strategy objects</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Observer</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Notify the user when something happens in the cart (item added, discount applied, total calculated)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Strategy is the most natural fit here — it directly solves the OCP violation that was the core problem from Phase 0. Observer adds event notifications which is realistic for any e-commerce system.</p>
