<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Then in Eclipse, right-click <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">docs/diagrams</code> folder → <strong>New → File</strong> → name it <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">architecture.png</code> — but don't create it there. Instead, just copy the saved PNG file into that folder using Windows Explorer:</p>
